@Node "Intro" "Introduction"

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

ML-Support is a tool for YAM and others mailers (with appropriate @{" module " Link "Plugin"})
which allows you to create subscribe/unsubscribe requests
for mailing list servers easily.

Simply enter all necessary data and choose if you want to subscribe or
unsubscribe. ML-Support will do the rest for you.

@EndNode

@Node "Legal" "Legal"

@{u}Legal@{uu}

ML-Support is Freeware. You use it on your own risk.

@EndNode

@Node "SysReq" "System Requirements"

@{u}System Requirements@{uu}

* an 68020+

* OS 3.0+

* @{" MUI " Link "MUI"} V3.3+
  It's recommended to use always the latest version.

* a @{" Mailcreatormodule " Link Plugin} for the mailer you use

@EndNode

@Node "Install" "Installation"

@{u}Installation@{uu}

Use the supplied Installer script.

You can set it up inside your mailer if it has something like
a 'Tools' menu. See the docs for the individual @{" modules " Link Plugin} about that.


@{u}To install by hand:@{uu}

Copy the ML-Support drawer where you want it.

Select a @{" Mailcreatormodule " Link Plugin} suitable for your mailer and
specify its name in one of these ways:

* Commandline argument: ML-Support <Modulename>
* Tooltype: CREATOR=<Modulename>

If present, the commandline argument overrides the Tooltype.

Attention: The modulename is case-sensitive! You must enter it
exactly the same as stated in the section describing the module.

@EndNode

@Node "Usage" "Usage"

@{u}Usage@{uu}

@{u}Mainwindow@{uu}

The List          shows the managed MLs

'Add'             adds an entry to the list and opens the Editwindow

'Clone'           creates a copy of the active entry

'Edit'            or a doubleclick on the entry opens the Editwindow
                  for that entry

'Remove'          deletes the selected entries from the list

'All'             selects all entries

'None'            deselects all entries

'Command'         selects if you want to subscribe, unsubscribe or
                  send another command to the list server

'Custom'          edit the string, which is sent to the list server
                  if 'Custom' is selected in 'Command', here

'Write'           creates the mails for the selected MLs
                  If you multiselect entries in the list then mails
                  for every selected entry are created

@{u}Project Menu@{uu}

'Merge...'        opens a filerequester to load a configfile and
                  merges it with the contents of the list

'About'           shows author and copyright info for ML-Support
'About MUI'       shows author and copyright info for MUI

'Quit'            quits ML-Support


@{u}Settings Menu@{uu}

'Save'            saves the list to the configfile

'MUI'             opens the MUI Config Window


@{u}Editwindow@{uu}

'ML Name'         edit the title of the ML here

'Subscribe Cmd'   edit the subscribe command of the ML here

'Unsubscribe Cmd' edit the unsubscribe command of the ML here

'Server Add.'     edit the email address of the list server here

'Add. Data'       select if you want to add your email address,
                  realname, email address & realname or
                  realname & email address to the command
                  The realname is not added when unsubscribing

'Comment'         you may make some notes here, it's not used anywhere
                  else but is saved also

'Subscribed?'     edit the subscription status here, if necessary

'Cmd. in To:'     place the command in the To: Header
                  See the bubblehelp for more info

'Ok'              accept changes

'Cancel'          discard changes

@EndNode

@Node "Plugin" "Mailcreator Plugins"

@{u}Mailcreator Plugins@{uu}

Look at @{" Installation " Link Install} for information on how to
setup a module.

Currently available modules

@{" YAM " Link Plug_YAM}

If your mailer isn't supported currently write to @{" me " Link Author},
or get the @{" Source Archive " Link Source} and write it yourself.

@EndNode

@Node "Plug_YAM" "YAM Module"

Modulename: YAM.mcc

This module is for use with YAM.

It works via ARexx.

You need YAM 2.1 or newer

You can set up ML-Support in the Scripts menu in YAM:

Open the Configwindow and go to the 'ARexx' page.
Set the cycle to 'AmigaDOS', enter the path to the ML-Support executeable
and add "YAM.mcc" (without the quotes).
Turn off 'Wait for termination'.

@EndNode

