@Node "History" "History"

@{u}History@{uu}

2.1        * Uses new 'Quiet' option in YAM 2.1
31.08.00   * Realname is no longer added when unsubscribing,
             since list servers don't seem to like it
           * Added string length checks all over the place
           * Added 'Merge' function to import configfiles
             (François-Xavier D'Hollander)

2.0        * Added a @{" Plug-in Interface " Link Plugin} which makes it possible to use
14.06.99     ML-Support with every mailer for which a plugin exists
           * The 'Subscribed?' checkmark was missing in the cyclechain
           * Added Installer script by Hervé Dupont
           * Added 'Comment' string in the Editwindow, suggested by
             Dr. Heiko Pollmeier

1.6        * Several optimizations to speedup operation
16.03.99   * Uses Pools to reduce memory fragmentation
           * Added Clone button
           * Fixed Enforcer Hit while saving
           * Shows the busypointer while creating mails
           * Some other internal improvements and cleanup

1.5        * The Command cycle shows the command which would change
07.02.99     your subscription status automatically
           * Fixed the nonprintable chars bug
           * The configfile is processed entirely in memory,
             this is much faster
           * Fixed the problems when using the MUI Prefs
           * The 'List changed' requester also appears when
             entries were removed from the list
           * The 'List changed' requester has now three options:
             Save and Quit, Quit, Cancel
           * ML-Support will keep running if saving the config
             on exit failed
           * Shows the busypointer while saving

1.4        * Now checks if YAM is running
26.01.99   * Recomplied with stormamiga.lib, this halved the size
             of the executeable
           * Redesigned the menus, added option to open the MUI Config
           * Shows the 'List changed' requester only if the List has
             really changed
           * Reorganized catalogs
           * Added french catalog and guide by Hervé Dupont
           * Added italian catalog by Francesco Mancuso

1.3        * The 'unsaved Changes' marker wasn't reset after saving
12.01.99   * Now it's possible to save an empty list
           * The list has an additional column which shows if you are
             subscribed to that ML.
             It's automatically set to the correct state, however you can
             edit it manually in the Editwindow.
           * Fixed layout problem with the checkmarks in the Editwindow
           * Locale support finished, added german catalog
           * Added some help bubbles

1.2        * Added option to place the command in the To: Header
05.01.99     (xxList-subscribe@nowhere.org) as suggested by Stephen Bridges
           * The list is sorted
           * Added warning if there are unsaved changes on exit
           * Errors while saving are reported now
           * The list is the default object

1.1        * Write button is disabled when the list is empty
04.01.99   * Write supports multiselect

1.0        * first release
30.12.98

@EndNode

